<br>
We love having our guild grow, and currently have been refining some policies which led to a temporary hold on recruitment.  Our hold has been lifted with the induction of our new charter and policies.<br>
<br>
Please browse our board, read our documents, and feel free to write a post.  If you are interested in becoming a Sentinel, please post your desire to do so here.  We would love to contact you ingame, group with you and get to know you.  <br>
<br>
Thank you for your interest in The Progeny Sentinels.  We look forward to meeting you ingame. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub73.ezboard.com/btheprogenysentinels47001.showUserPublicProfile?gid=leahnorahaeldulphus>Leahnorah Aeldulphus</A> at: 1/31/03 5:03:46 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub73.ezboard.com/btheprogenysentinels47001.showUserPublicProfile?gid=leahnora>Leahnora</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Board Administrator</span><br>  Posts: 54<br> <font color=#333333>(12/5/02 9:10:38 am)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Recruitment</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline"><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Recruitment Policy for The Progeny Sentinels</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--><br>
<br>
1. Only classes and races of neutral/good alignment will be permitted candidacy and membership, with the exception of Jorgie, who is written into the guild's history and charter.<br>
<br>
2. A person must be at least of the 15th level to become a candidate.  Alternates of members may join the guild at any level.<br>
<br>
3. A person must post on the TPS EZboard application forum in order to begin the process of seeking candidacy in the guild.  The post must include the character's race, class, level, and a description of what the person wants in a guild and why the person is seeking membership in TPS.  The person may also submit an email address to where the guild's charter and policies will be emailed.  <br>
<br>
4. A person must have 3 officers of TPS who are willing to sponsor him/her in order to become a candidate in TPS.  <br>
<br>
5. A sponsor must chat and/or group with the person considering membership in order to be able to vouch for that person's character, skills, sportsmanship, behavior, and interactions with people, in accordance with the guild's Code of Conduct.  <br>
<br>
6. A sponsor must post on the TPS EZboard application forum who he/she is sponsoring.  Prospective candidates must post on the TPSEZboard forum who they have gained sponsorship from.  Candidates, members and prospective candidates of TPS must post interactions between prospective candidates and guildmembers on the TPSEZboard application forum.<br>
<br>
7. A prospective candidate may receive an invitation to become a TPS candidate after he/she has completed the above steps and posted a request for a /guildinvite on his/her application.  Any officer may issue the invitation after the above steps have been completed.  It is the responsibility of this officer to state the guild's membership policy to the prospective candidate before issuing an invitation.  The prospective candidate must also affirm that he/she agrees to the stated policies.  The officer may then issue an invitation to the prospective candidate.<br>
<br>
8. A TPS officer who has invited a prospective candidate into the guild must post the date he/she invited said candidate into the guild.  This date begins the person's candidacy period.<br>
<br>
9. A candidacy period will last for no less than 3 weeks.<br>
Privileges and restrictions of a candidate are the following:<br>
--Candidates will be invited into the guild. <br>
--Candidates will be permitted to join guildchat, and aol and tga chat channels.  Candidates will not be permitted to join the TGANews channel.<br>
--Candidates may not have an alt in the guild.<br>
--Candidates will have access to candidate sections of the TPSEZboard.  Candidates will not have access to officers-only chat channels or sections of the TPSEZboard, and not have a say in the government of the guild.  <br>
--Candidates will be permitted to lead raids.  <br>
--Candidates will not be permitted to use guildvaults of any kind.  A guild member may give/lend a candidate items out of a personal bank, but not from a guild bank. <br>
--Candidates will be included in randoms for loot on general raids and exp groups.<br>
--Raid leaders will determine whether or not to include candidates in randoms/awards involving loot for epic pieces, quested armor, and special drops from high-end mobs.  This decision must be made and announced prior to the raid, otherwise candidates will be included on randoms/awards the same as guild members.<br>
<br>
10. Candidates will be voted on by all officers of the guild no less than 3 weeks after the initiation of their candidacy.  Voting on candidates for membership will last for a minimum of 1 week.  <br>
<br>
11. Any TPS member may begin a poll to vote on a candidate.<br>
Three options will be on the poll: Aye, Nay, and Need more time.  &quot;Need more time&quot; will be for those that do not yet know the candidate well enough to decide whether or not the candidate should become a member.  Anyone voting Nay on a given candidate is encouraged to explain their reason in full on the poll thread. <br>
<br>
12. A candidate will pass into membership by a majority of votes, with two nays permitted.  If &quot;need more time&quot; is at least one-third of the vote, then the candidacy period will be extended by one week.  Members who submitted a &quot;need more time&quot; vote must post aye or nay once they have decided their vote.  At the end of that week, the ayes and nays (including the posted ones) will be tallied.  If someone posted a &quot;need more time&quot; but did not later post an &quot;aye&quot; or &quot;nay&quot;, the &quot;aye&quot; and &quot;nay&quot; votes and posts will be tallied.<br>
<br>
13. Only a TPSEZBoard Administrator may formally announce the advancement of a candidate to membership level (this is due to changes that must be made on the EZBoard regarding EZBoard access privileges).  <br>
